HEADWORD: Hostel
<hw>Hos"tel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hostel</ets>, <ets>ostel</ets>, OF. <ets>hostel</ets>,
<ets>ostel</ets>, LL. <ets>hospitale</ets>, <ets>hospitalis</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>hospitalis</ets>. See <er>Hospital</er>, and cf.
<er>Hotel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inn.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Poe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So pass I <qex>hostel</qex>, hall, and grange.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A small, unendowed college in Oxford or
Cambridge.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

